1.02	Cardiff_Lions	Cardiff Lions	The Cardiff Lions RFC (Welsh: ) is a gay and gay friendly rugby union football club based in Cardiff, Wales. The club was founded in 2004 and remains the only gay rugby club in Wales. The Lions were admitted as members of the International Gay Rugby Association and Board in 2006.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b7/CLLogo150.jpg
